for inline....
<p style="color: blue;background-color: grey;">
to make a style block..
<style>
p{
color: red;
}--all the p tags will change red.
</style>
adding more styles...
for class
.blue-text{
color: blue;
}for having a class blue-text.
chaning font size..
font-size: 30px;
font-family: monospace--->letters style
import fonts from google..
<link href="" rel="stylesheet"type="text/css">
h2{
font-family: Lobster,'Open Sans'-->for backup fonts;
}
.large{
width: 500px;
}
adding borders...
border-family: Lobster;
border-color: green;
border-width: 10px;
border-style: solid;
border-radius: 10px; if in % it makes a circle
set the id of an element....
for id attribute:
#idname{
color: blue;
}-->giving higher preference to id than class,and one id for one element.
adjust the padding...
eg:padding: 20px;
adjust the margin..
eg:margin: 20px;
add different padding:
padding-top: 40px;
padding-right: 40 px;
padding-left: 20 px;
padding-bottom:20 px;
use clockwise notation to specify the margin--
margin: 40px 20px 20px 30px;


<style>
[type='radio']{
margin: 20px;
</style>
understand absolute versus relative units-->
!important--->overriding all other styles.
use hex code....
background-color: #000000;-->black
background-color: rgb(255,255,255)--white
u can mix colors;
background-color: rgb(255,112,214);







